ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: system_monitor
ⲃⲉⲣⲥⲓⲟⲛ: "1.0.0"
ⲗⲁⲛⲅⲩⲁⲅⲉ: 999
ⲙⲟⲇⲩⲗⲉ: system_monitor

ⲥⲣⲉⲁⲧⲓⲟⲛ_ⲡⲁⲧⲧⲉⲣⲛ:
  ⲥⲟⲩⲣⲥⲉ: SystemMetrics
  ⲧⲣⲁⲛⲥⲫⲟⲣⲙⲉⲣ: PerformanceAnalyzer
  ⲣⲉⲥⲩⲗⲧ: HealthReport

ⲃⲉⲏⲁⲃⲓⲟⲣⲥ:
  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: collect_metrics
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: System components to monitor
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Gather performance metrics from all .999 files
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return comprehensive metrics report
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: full_system_metrics
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {components: ["all"], interval: "5min"}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {cpu_usage: 0.45, memory_efficiency: 0.82, file_count: 150}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: detect_anomalies
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Metrics data and baseline performance
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Identify performance degradation or unusual patterns
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return anomaly alerts with severity levels
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: performance_anomaly
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {metric: "memory_usage", current: 0.95, baseline: 0.75}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {anomaly_detected: true, severity: "high", action: "optimize"}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: trigger_evolution
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Anomaly reports and evolution thresholds
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Determine if system needs evolutionary improvements
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return evolution triggers with priorities
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: evolution_needed
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {anomalies: ["memory_leak", "slow_queries"], threshold: 0.8}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {trigger_evolution: true, priority: "critical", target: "memory.999"}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: generate_reports
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Monitoring data and time periods
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Create detailed performance reports
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return formatted reports for analysis
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: daily_report
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {period: "24h", format: "comprehensive"}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {report_generated: true, insights: ["memory_optimized", "cpu_improved"]}